# Ignore-file for the root Go `Dockerfile`. BuildKit resolves a Dockerfile-adjacent
# <dockerfile>.dockerignore ahead of the root .dockerignore, so this file governs the
# Go image context while the SPA builds (frontend/<app>/Dockerfile) keep using the
# root .dockerignore. KEEP go.mod, go.sum, cmd/**, internal/** — everything the Go
# build needs; exclude everything else to keep the context small and the cache stable.

# Frontend / Node — never part of a Go image
node_modules
**/node_modules
frontend
packages
package.json
pnpm-lock.yaml
pnpm-workspace.yaml
Caddyfile
**/dist
**/.vite
**/.verify

# VCS / CI / tooling / docs
.git
.github
.claude
backlog
docs
e2e
*.md

# DB tooling — not needed to compile a service binary. `migrations/` is the
# exception (M2-12): the gateway embeds migrations/*.sql via go:embed
# (migrations.md §2), so they MUST be in the Go build context or the gateway image
# fails to compile. It is a shared Dockerfile, so migrations/ lands in every
# service's context; the seven context services simply never import it.
db
Makefile
docker-compose.yml

# Docker / env / editor / OS
Dockerfile
Dockerfile.dockerignore
.dockerignore
.env
.env.*
**/.env
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
